    <title>Awesome Roasted Beetroot Dip</title>
    <filename>awesome_roasted_beetroot_dip.xml</filename>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/beetroot_dip.jpeg</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
  
    <diet>FODMAP</diet>
    <diet>Vegan</diet>

    <ingredient>4 Beetroots</ingredient>
    <ingredient>4 tbsp olive oil</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 teaspoon cumin</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 teaspoon coriander</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 teaspoon salt</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 chilli</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 tbsp lemon juice </ingredient>

    <step>
Peel and chop beets and place on oven tray. Drizzle 2 tbsp olive oil over beets and toss to coat. Place in moderate preheated (180C) oven for 45 mins, and turn 2 times.  Once done allow to cool completely on the tray.  Place in blender, with remaining ingredients and blend until desired consistency (about 3-4 minutes.) Serve with something crunchy!
    </step>
</recipe>